question: 一番目
sourceMnemonic: You've seen <ja>一番</ja> (number one), so what in the world is this eye on the end? This eye (<ja>目</ja>) signifies the order. So, add this to "number one" and you have the <vocabulary>first thing</vocabulary> / <vocabulary>the first</vocabulary>.
sourceReadingMnemonic: The reading for this word is just the vocab word <ja>一番</ja> plus the word <ja>目</ja>. If you know both of those readings you'll be able to read this one as well.
